<H3> <TI>   Kakizawa on Exceptions to DPRK Remittances Ban </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kakizawa on Exceptions to DPRK Remittances Ban </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0806042894 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 8 Jun 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0806042894 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 7 June Evening Edition] </F>
  [Text] At a news conference after the cabinet meeting on 7 
June, Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa commented on the possible 
ban on North Koreans in Japan making remittances to their home 
country, a move which is being considered as part of economic 
sanctions against the DRPK over the issue of its suspected 
development of nuclear arms. 
  He said: "Similar cases in the past have provided for some 
exceptions on humanitarian grounds." He indicated that if 
sanctions were be imposed, some exceptions would be provided on 
humanitarian grounds. 

</TEXT>

