BFN 

  [Text] According to a correspondent's report, on 2 June 
Surin Deputy Governor Phanat Sakuntanat signed an announcement 
opening the border trading point at Chom Pass, Kap Choeng 
District on 4 June. This trading point has been closed and 
reopened several times due to fighting in nearby parts of 
Cambodia. 
  Meanwhile, a source familiar with the Cambodian border in 
Surin Province noted that kidnapping of Thai citizens for ransom 
was mostly the result of business blackmail, not hunger. The 
problem of Cambodian bandits robbing Thais existed long before 
border points were opened for trading. 

