<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 5 (KCNA) -- About 2,000 workers 
affiliated with the subway trade union council held a rally in 
the Chongmyo Park in Seoul on June 2 and vowed to win in the 
wage-hike struggle for 1994, a Seoul-based radio reported. 
  Pointing to the instability of working conditions, the 
workers at the rally called for the enforcement of an 8-hour 
workday. 
  They rejected the wage hike draft agreed upon between the 
subsidized South Korean General Federation of Trade Unions 
(Nochong) and the general federation of managers councils and 
demanded a wage hike up to a level sufficient to ensure living. 

