<F P=106> [Report by Sin Yong-su from Beijing] </F>
  [Text] There have been some reports that Chinese President 
Jiang Zemin warned North Korea to accept negotiations on the 
nuclear issue when he met on 7 June with Choe Kwang, chief of 
general staff of North Korea's Army during his visit to China. 
However, it has been learned this is not true. 
  One high-ranking official of the ROK Embassy in China said: 
I understand that President Jiang did not make a detailed 
mention of North Korea's nuclear issue, but only confirmed the 
traditional friendship between the two countries when he met 
with Chief of General Staff Choe. 

