actually seeking heightened tensions and military adventures, 
remaining captive to the consciousness of confrontation and war 
psychology. 
  The United States is even scheming to send U.S. 
reinforcements to the Korean front from Alaska and Germany and 
50 warships, more than 200 warplanes and a U.S. naval force 
25,000 strong based in Hawaii have started for the Korean waters. 
  It is a mistake to try to subdue and stifle the DPRK by 
strength. The hardline conservatives of the United States seem 
to be ignorant of our faith and might. We regard independence 
and socialism as our life and blood. We are resolved and ready 
to counter any military option of the United States. 

