<H3> <TI>   Further Reports on Reaction to DPRK Related Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reports on Reaction to DPRK Related Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Vice Minister on DPRK-IAEA Talks </H4>

<F P=102> OW0706020694 Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database in Japanese 7 Jun 
94 -- FOR OOFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0706020694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo Nikkei Telecom Database </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 7 Jun Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] Speaking at a press conference on 6 June in 
connection with North Korea's suspected nuclear weapons 
development, Vice Foreign Minister Saito indicated there was 
still a possibility that negotiations would be held between 
North Korea and the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), 
depending on the next move by Pyongyang. 
  Saito said: "The IAEA's report says 'North Korea's overall 
cooperation is necessary to satisfactory inspections.' This 
means that the possibility of conducting inspections by other 
means has not been eliminated." 
  He cited special inspections of two nuclear-related 
facilities which have not been filed for inspection as potential 
"other ways" in which inspections might be carried out. 

</TEXT>

