<H3> <TI>   Further Reports on Reaction to DPRK Related Issues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further Reports on Reaction to DPRK Related Issues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    LDP Head Opposes Indenpendent Sanctions </H4>

<F P=102> OW0706125194 Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN in Japanese 6 Jun 94 
Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0706125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo MAINICHI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a 5 June news conference in Fukuoka city, 
Liberal Democratic Party President Yohei Kono commented on the 
trilateral talks among Japan, the United States, and the ROK on 
the DPRK's suspected nuclear development program. He said: "I 
hope the three countries will fully discuss measures to have a 
UN resolution adopted." 
  His remark indicates that he is opposed to the government's 
positive stance on a plan for Japan, the United States, and 
South Korea to independently impose sanctions on North Korea if 
the UN Security Council fails to adopt a resolution calling for 
sanctions. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

