<F P=101> Japan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hata Supports New Group To Counter LDP </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Supports New Group To Counter LDP </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW0806185594 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 7 Jun 94 
Evening Edition p 1 -- FOR OFFCIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW0806185594 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In a speech to a Democratic Socialist Party 
convention on the morning of 7 June, Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata 
said: "We have to form a political group capable of competing 
against the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] and taking the reins 
of government in a dignified manner." In this way, he again 
indicated that he would make the Hata administration a 
full-fledged government and carry out political reorganization 
while considering forming a new political party. 
  After attending the convention, Hata returned to the prime 
minister's official residence. There, he was asked by reporters 
about his speech at the convention. Hata said: "The hasty 
formation of (new parliamentary group) `Kaishin' created 
confusion. So, we have to proceed slowly next time. In the 
initial stage, the political group I mentioned should function 
as a parliamentary group. But in the future, I think it should 
become a political party." His remark suggests that he will 
first form a new parliamentary group that includes the Social 
Democratic Party of Japan. 

</TEXT>

