<F P=106> [From NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN 8 Jun Morning Edition] </F>
  [Text] A policy study group comprising of 44 dietmen from 
both the Liberal Democratic Party [LDP] and Social Democratic 
Party of Japan [SDPJ] was begun on 7 June. Among its leaders 
are LDP Deputy Secretary-General Kamei and Vice Chariman Yasuo 
Yamashita of the SDPJ Diet Policy Committee. Five SPDJ dietmen 
and 30 LDP dietmen attended the group's first session held at 
the Dietmen's Hall on 7 June. It was decided at the meeting 
that the group will meet once a week to exchange views on such 
topics as basic policies on foreign affairs, security, and other 
issues as well as prospects for the political situation. 

